<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">DCS service</p>
    <h2>DCS by Fisher & Paykel: best longevity reputation in the premium grill field.</h2>

    <p>DCS (Dynamic Cooking Systems) is the premium outdoor grill brand from Fisher & Paykel Appliances, which has been part of the Haier Group since 2012. US headquarters in Costa Mesa, California. Among premium outdoor grills, DCS has the best component longevity reputation we see in the field. Owners routinely run BGB and BGA series 12 to 15 years with just ceramic radiant rod replacement and standard wear-item maintenance. The U-burner stainless construction and 120VAC electronic ignition are reliable to a fault.</p>

    <p>Our techs service the entire DCS lineup across decades: BGB-series built-ins (current), BGA-series, BGC, BGE legacy units, the Series 9 Evolution BE1-series flagship (BE1-36RC-N and similar), the Professional BH1 36 and 48 inch line, and legacy DCS27 / DCS36 / DCS48 cart-mounted units. Plus DCS side burners, warming drawers (WD30 series), and outdoor refrigeration accessories.</p>

    <p>CSLB #1138898. Same-day across LA, Orange County, Ventura. EPA 608 certified for DCS outdoor refrigeration components, which is required for any unit with sealed-system refrigerant work.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP & WHAT FAILS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Lineup and architecture</p>
    <h2>DCS series and what fails on each.</h2>

    <p class="lead">DCS uses series-coded model numbering. BGB is current built-in flagship. BGA, BGC, BGE are earlier generations. BE1 is the Series 9 Evolution flagship. BH1 is the newer Professional naming. We identify by serial number first, not just model badge.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">BGB Series (current built-in flagship: BGB30, BGB36, BGB48)</h3>
    <p>Current production. 120VAC electronic ignition, U-burner construction, ceramic radiant rods between burners and cooking grates. Common service items in chronological order:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Years 5 to 10:</strong> Ceramic radiant rods crack from heat shock. OEM 245398 (9.5 inch rods, sold in packs of 10), replaced as needed per zone. The Radiant Assembly BGB36/48 (OEM 214081) is the full assembly if multiple rods are gone or the housing is damaged. Includes housing 213997 and lock 214046.</li>
      <li><strong>Years 7 to 12:</strong> Igniter electrode replacement, per zone. U-burner architecture means each main burner has its own electrode.</li>
      <li><strong>Years 8 to 15:</strong> Stainless cooking grate replacement (OEM 212341 BGA GRATES). Lifetime warranty on these for the original purchaser.</li>
      <li><strong>Years 10 to 15:</strong> Heat shield firebox plate replacement (OEM 214569). Gradual corrosion from drippings and thermal cycling.</li>
      <li><strong>Years 12+:</strong> U-burner pinhole on coastal installs. Coastal salt is the limiting factor on otherwise lifetime-rated burners.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">BGA Series (older built-in: BGA36, BGA48)</h3>
    <p>Earlier generation BGB. Many parts shared (cooking grates, ceramic rods). Different control panel and wiring harness. Still excellent parts availability through Fisher & Paykel customer care (1-888-936-7872).</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">BGC, BGE Series (older built-in, pre-2010)</h3>
    <p>Pre-2010 generation. Parts availability decreasing on some control components. We still service these. Most often the work is ceramic radiants, igniter electrodes, and cooking grates, all current parts that fit older models.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">BE1 Series 9 Evolution (flagship: BE1-36RC-N, BE1-48RC, BE1-30 variants)</h3>
    <p>Current flagship. The 36 inch with rotisserie (suffix RC) is the most common variant. Service profile similar to BGB but with additional rotisserie components and updated control electronics. Manuals available through Fisher & Paykel.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">BH1 Professional Series (36 inch and 48 inch)</h3>
    <p>Newer DCS Professional naming. Same general architecture as BGB and BE1 with updated cosmetics and control panel.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Legacy DCS27, DCS36, DCS48 cart-mounted (pre-2010)</h3>
    <p>Earlier cart-mounted units. Parts availability varies. Some control panel and electronic components are no longer made. Burners, cooking grates, and ceramic radiants typically still available.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Side Burners, Warming Drawers, Power Burners</h3>
    <p>DCS side burners and WD30 warming drawers. Service profile similar to other premium brands: gas valve seizure after inactivity, igniter electrode failures, controller issues at 8+ years.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 TYPICAL SCENARIOS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top DCS repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>

    <p>In rough order of frequency on DCS service calls:</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Ceramic radiant rod cracks (any series, year 5 to 10).</strong> Single rod cracked or shattered from heat shock. Replace per zone with OEM 245398 (9.5 inch rods). Most common DCS repair we do.</li>
      <li><strong>Multiple ceramic radiants gone (year 8 to 12).</strong> Owner has been running with cracked rods for years. Replace full Radiant Assembly OEM 214081 (includes housing 213997 and lock 214046).</li>
      <li><strong>Igniter electrode failure (any series, year 7 to 12).</strong> Single zone won't light, others working. Per-zone electrode replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Burner valve seizure after seasonal inactivity.</strong> Gas valve sticks. Disassemble, clean, lubricate. Sometimes requires valve replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>U-burner pinhole at coastal installs (12+ years).</strong> Stainless develops a pinhole. Replace burner before manifold damage.</li>
      <li><strong>Stainless cooking grate replacement.</strong> Wear over 8 to 15 years. Lifetime warranty processing through Fisher & Paykel for the original purchaser.</li>
      <li><strong>Heat shield firebox plate replacement.</strong> Gradual corrosion. OEM 214569 replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Rotisserie components (BE1-RC variants).</strong> Motor seizure or spit rod warping. Replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Control panel issues (BGB current production).</strong> Wire harness corrosion at the connector, switch pitting. Less common but happens.</li>
      <li><strong>Smoker box assembly issues.</strong> Older BGB and BGA smoker boxes, runners burn through along the top edge. Replacement.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five DCS jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills, DCS BGB36-BQARN (2014 install)</h3>
        <p>Middle zone wasn't producing even heat. Inspected: ceramic radiant rod cracked across the full 9.5 inch length, partial second crack starting on adjacent rod. Replaced 2 rods with OEM 245398. Inspected remaining 4 rods, all serviceable. Total: $120 plus $95 parts plus 30 minutes = $245. 11-year-old grill back to original heat distribution.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Newport Beach, DCS BE1-36RC-N (2019 install)</h3>
        <p>Left burner ceramic radiant cracked. Replaced single radiant. While there, inspected other 3 zones. One had a hairline crack starting that would have failed within months. Replaced both. Total: $120 plus $95 (2 rods) plus 45 minutes = $260. Customer agreed because the second radiant catch saved a future service call.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pacific Palisades, DCS BGB48-BQARL (2010 install)</h3>
        <p>Multiple ignition zones failing. Diagnosed: 4 of 4 igniter electrodes degraded at 14 years (well beyond typical 7 to 12 year service life). Replaced all electrodes simultaneously. Tested ignition cycle. Working. Total: $120 plus $480 (4 electrodes) plus 1.5 hours = $740.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Calabasas, DCS BH1 36 inch Professional (2022 install)</h3>
        <p>Won't ignite at all on a cold January morning. Diagnosed: outdoor GFCI receptacle had tripped from water intrusion (DCS uses 120VAC mains power, not battery). Reset GFCI. Tested all zones. Working. Charged $120 diagnostic only. Customer didn't realize DCS needed mains power and there was no battery to check.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Malibu, DCS BGA36-BQARN (2008 install)</h3>
        <p>16-year-old grill. Owner asking if it was worth repairing or time to replace. Multiple issues: 3 ceramic radiants gone, 2 burners with pinholes (coastal salt), control panel switch worn. Diagnosed and quoted $1,250 to bring it fully back to spec. Owner did the math; replacement equivalent grill installed runs $7,500+. Approved repair. Spent 4.5 hours on the work. Customer got another 5 to 7 years out of the grill.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2>What we do for DCS, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>All BGB-series built-ins (BGB30, BGB36, BGB48, current and prior generations)</li>
      <li>BGA-series built-ins (BGA36, BGA48)</li>
      <li>BGC, BGE legacy built-ins (pre-2010)</li>
      <li>BE1 Series 9 Evolution (BE1-36RC-N, BE1-48RC, BE1-30 variants)</li>
      <li>BH1 Professional Series (36 inch, 48 inch)</li>
      <li>Legacy DCS27, DCS36, DCS48 cart-mounted units</li>
      <li>DCS side burners</li>
      <li>DCS warming drawers (WD30 series)</li>
      <li>DCS power burners</li>
      <li>DCS outdoor refrigeration accessories (EPA 608 required, we have it)</li>
      <li>Lifetime warranty processing through Fisher & Paykel for warranty-eligible parts</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new DCS grill installation (warranty installs go through the authorized Fisher & Paykel / DCS dealer network); custom DCS cabinetry modification (metal fabricator trade, not appliance repair); wood-fired pizza oven products under the DCS or Fisher & Paykel umbrella (we do gas-fired only).</p>

    <p>For warranty-eligible repairs (lifetime warranty applies to many DCS components), we document the failure and help process claims with Fisher & Paykel customer care at 1-888-936-7872. Replacement parts ship to you, we install. Labor is separately billable but minimal compared to out-of-pocket parts purchase.</p>
  </div>
</section>

