<!-- 07 WHY US -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Why us for DCS</p>
    <h2>What separates our DCS service from general grill repair.</h2>

    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>Ceramic radiant expertise.</strong> This is the number-one DCS repair. Knowing which rods to replace, when, and how to inspect remaining rods for hairline cracks. We do this multiple times per week.</li>
      <li><strong>U-burner specialists.</strong> DCS U-burner architecture is shared with Twin Eagles and a few other premium brands. We know the failure patterns.</li>
      <li><strong>120VAC awareness.</strong> DCS uses mains power, not batteries. When customers think "battery" first (because Lynx and Sedona have batteries), they miss the actual issue. We diagnose at the GFCI and mains supply first.</li>
      <li><strong>Lifetime warranty processing.</strong> Many DCS components have lifetime warranty. We help process claims through Fisher & Paykel customer care so you don't pay for parts that should be free.</li>
      <li><strong>Coastal salt expertise.</strong> Malibu, Newport Beach, Pacific Palisades. Coastal failure patterns specific to DCS' otherwise excellent stainless construction are about 35% of our brand work.</li>
      <li><strong>EPA 608 certified.</strong> DCS outdoor refrigeration components require certification for any sealed-system refrigerant work.</li>
      <li><strong>CSLB #1138898 plus BBB A+.</strong> Verifiable with the state and the bureau.</li>
